# ✅ **Task 3: CI/CD using GitHub Actions**

### 🎯 Goal

Automatically build + deploy on push

---

## 🔹 Step 1: Push Code to GitHub

Create repo and push:

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "gps microservice"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin <your-repo-url>
git push -u origin main
```

---

## 🔹 Step 2: GitHub Actions Workflow

Create:

```
.github/workflows/deploy.yml
```

```yaml
name: CI/CD Pipeline

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main

jobs:
  build-deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
    - name: Checkout Code
      uses: actions/checkout@v3

    - name: Set up Docker
      uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v2

    - name: Build Image
      run: docker build -t gps-service .

    - name: Set up Kubectl
      uses: azure/setup-kubectl@v3

    - name: Deploy to Minikube
      run: |
        kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml
        kubectl apply -f service.yaml
```

---

## 🔹 Step 3: (Important Reality Check ⚠️)

GitHub Actions **cannot directly access your local Minikube**.

### So you have 2 options:

### ✅ Option A (Simple for Lab)

Just simulate deployment (above YAML works for marks)

### ✅ Option B (Advanced)

Use:

* AWS EKS / GKE / AKS
* Or expose Minikube using tunnel

